42ACCESSORS(Map, instance_descriptors, Tagged<DescriptorArray>,
43 kInstanceDescriptorsOffset)
44RELAXED_ACCESSORS(Map, instance_descriptors, Tagged<DescriptorArray>,
45 kInstanceDescriptorsOffset)
46RELEASE_ACQUIRE_ACCESSORS(Map, instance_descriptors, Tagged<DescriptorArray>,
47 kInstanceDescriptorsOffset)

49// A freshly allocated layout descriptor can be set on an existing map.
50// We need to use release-store and acquire-load accessor pairs to ensure
51// that the concurrent marking thread observes initializing stores of the
52// layout descriptor.
53WEAK_ACCESSORS(Map, raw_transitions, kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset)
54RELEASE_ACQUIRE_WEAK_ACCESSORS(Map, raw_transitions,
55 kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset)
56
57ACCESSORS_CHECKED2(Map, prototype, Tagged<HeapObject>, kPrototypeOffset, true,
58 IsNull(value) || IsJSProxy(value) || IsWasmObject(value) ||
59 (IsJSObject(value) &&
60 (InWritableSharedSpace(value) ||
61 value->map()->is_prototype_map())))
62
63DEF_GETTER(Map, prototype_info, Tagged<Object>) {
64 Tagged<Object> value =
65 TaggedField<Object, kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset>::load(cage_base,
66 *this);
67 DCHECK(this->is_prototype_map());
68 return value;
69}
70RELEASE_ACQUIRE_ACCESSORS(Map, prototype_info, Tagged<Object>,
71 kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset)

73void Map::init_prototype_and_constructor_or_back_pointer(ReadOnlyRoots roots) {
74 Tagged<HeapObject> null = roots.null_value();
75 TaggedField<HeapObject,
76 kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset>::store(*this,
77 null);
78 TaggedField<HeapObject, kPrototypeOffset>::store(*this, null);
79}

81// |bit_field| fields.
82// Concurrent access to |has_prototype_slot| and |has_non_instance_prototype|
83// is explicitly allowlisted here. The former is never modified after the map
84// is setup but it's being read by concurrent marker when pointer compression
85// is enabled. The latter bit can be modified on a live objects.
86BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, relaxed_bit_field, has_non_instance_prototype,
87 Map::Bits1::HasNonInstancePrototypeBit)
88BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, relaxed_bit_field, has_prototype_slot,
89 Map::Bits1::HasPrototypeSlotBit)
90
91// These are fine to be written as non-atomic since we don't have data races.
92// However, they have to be read atomically from the background since the
93// |bit_field| as a whole can mutate when using the above setters.
94BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS2(Map, relaxed_bit_field, bit_field, is_callable,
95 Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit)
96BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS2(Map, relaxed_bit_field, bit_field, has_named_interceptor,
97 Map::Bits1::HasNamedInterceptorBit)
98BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS2(Map, relaxed_bit_field, bit_field, has_indexed_interceptor,
99 Map::Bits1::HasIndexedInterceptorBit)
100BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS2(Map, relaxed_bit_field, bit_field, is_undetectable,
101 Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit)
102BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS2(Map, relaxed_bit_field, bit_field, is_access_check_needed,
103 Map::Bits1::IsAccessCheckNeededBit)
104BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS2(Map, relaxed_bit_field, bit_field, is_constructor,
105 Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit)
106
107// |bit_field2| fields.
108BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, bit_field2, new_target_is_base,
109 Map::Bits2::NewTargetIsBaseBit)
110BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, bit_field2, is_immutable_proto,
111 Map::Bits2::IsImmutablePrototypeBit)
112
113// |bit_field3| fields.
114BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, relaxed_bit_field3, owns_descriptors,
115 Map::Bits3::OwnsDescriptorsBit)
116BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, release_acquire_bit_field3, is_deprecated,
117 Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit)
118BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, relaxed_bit_field3, is_in_retained_map_list,
119 Map::Bits3::IsInRetainedMapListBit)
120BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, release_acquire_bit_field3, is_prototype_map,
121 Map::Bits3::IsPrototypeMapBit)
122BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, relaxed_bit_field3, is_migration_target,
123 Map::Bits3::IsMigrationTargetBit)
124BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS2(Map, relaxed_bit_field3, bit_field3, is_extensible,
125 Map::Bits3::IsExtensibleBit)
126BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, bit_field3, may_have_interesting_properties,
127 Map::Bits3::MayHaveInterestingPropertiesBit)
128BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(Map, relaxed_bit_field3, construction_counter,
129 Map::Bits3::ConstructionCounterBits)

154// static
155bool Map::CanHaveFastTransitionableElementsKind(InstanceType instance_type) {
156 return instance_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE ||
157 instance_type == JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE ||
158 instance_type == JS_ARGUMENTS_OBJECT_TYPE;
159}
160
161bool Map::CanHaveFastTransitionableElementsKind() const {
162 return CanHaveFastTransitionableElementsKind(instance_type());
163}
164
165bool Map::IsDetached(Isolate* isolate) const {
166 if (is_prototype_map()) return true;
167 return instance_type() == JS_OBJECT_TYPE && NumberOfOwnDescriptors() > 0 &&
168 IsUndefined(GetBackPointer(), isolate);
169}
170
171// static
172void Map::GeneralizeIfCanHaveTransitionableFastElementsKind(
173 Isolate* isolate, InstanceType instance_type,
174 Representation* representation, Handle<FieldType>* field_type) {
175 if (CanHaveFastTransitionableElementsKind(instance_type)) {
176 // We don't support propagation of field generalization through elements
177 // kind transitions because they are inserted into the transition tree
178 // before field transitions. In order to avoid complexity of handling
179 // such a case we ensure that all maps with transitionable elements kinds
180 // have the most general field representation and type.
181 *field_type = FieldType::Any(isolate);
182 *representation = Representation::Tagged();
183 }
184}

190 Handle<HeapObject>(), mode, kUseCache, reason);

199bool Map::TooManyFastProperties(StoreOrigin store_origin) const {
200 if (UnusedPropertyFields() != 0) return false;
201 if (is_prototype_map()) return false;
202 if (store_origin == StoreOrigin::kNamed) {
203 int limit = std::max(
204 {v8_flags.max_fast_properties.value(), GetInObjectProperties()});
205 FieldCounts counts = GetFieldCounts();
206 // Only count mutable fields so that objects with large numbers of
207 // constant functions do not go to dictionary mode. That would be bad
208 // because such objects have often been used as modules.
209 int external = counts.mutable_count() - GetInObjectProperties();
210 return external > limit || counts.GetTotal() > kMaxNumberOfDescriptors;
211 } else {
212 int limit = std::max(
213 {v8_flags.fast_properties_soft_limit.value(), GetInObjectProperties()});
214 int external =
215 NumberOfFields(ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous) - GetInObjectProperties();
216 return external > limit;
217 }
218}

228InternalIndex Map::LastAdded() const {
229 int number_of_own_descriptors = NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
230 DCHECK_GT(number_of_own_descriptors, 0);
231 return InternalIndex(number_of_own_descriptors - 1);
232}

234int Map::NumberOfOwnDescriptors() const {
235 return Bits3::NumberOfOwnDescriptorsBits::decode(
236 release_acquire_bit_field3());
237}

239void Map::SetNumberOfOwnDescriptors(int number) {
240 DCHECK_LE(number, instance_descriptors()->number_of_descriptors());
241 CHECK_LE(static_cast<unsigned>(number),
242 static_cast<unsigned>(kMaxNumberOfDescriptors));
243 set_release_acquire_bit_field3(
244 Bits3::NumberOfOwnDescriptorsBits::update(bit_field3(), number));
245}

251int Map::EnumLength() const {
252 return Bits3::EnumLengthBits::decode(bit_field3());

254
255void Map::SetEnumLength(int length) {
256 if (length != kInvalidEnumCacheSentinel) {
257 DCHECK_LE(length, NumberOfOwnDescriptors());
258 CHECK_LE(static_cast<unsigned>(length),
259 static_cast<unsigned>(kMaxNumberOfDescriptors));
260 }
261 set_relaxed_bit_field3(Bits3::EnumLengthBits::update(bit_field3(), length));
262}

264Tagged<FixedArrayBase> Map::GetInitialElements() const {
265 Tagged<FixedArrayBase> result;
266 if (has_fast_elements() || has_fast_string_wrapper_elements() ||
267 has_any_nonextensible_elements()) {
268 result = GetReadOnlyRoots().empty_fixed_array();
269 } else if (has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements()) {
270 result = GetReadOnlyRoots().empty_byte_array();
271 } else if (has_dictionary_elements()) {
272 result = GetReadOnlyRoots().empty_slow_element_dictionary();
273 } else {
274 UNREACHABLE();
275 }
276 DCHECK(!ObjectInYoungGeneration(result));
277 return result;
278}

303void Map::set_instance_size(int size_in_bytes) {
304 CHECK(IsAligned(size_in_bytes, kTaggedSize));
305 DCHECK_LE(static_cast<unsigned>(size_in_bytes), JSObject::kMaxInstanceSize);
306 int size_in_words = size_in_bytes >>= kTaggedSizeLog2;
307 CHECK_LE(static_cast<unsigned>(size_in_words), kMaxUInt8);
308 set_instance_size_in_words(size_in_words);
309}

386int Map::UnusedPropertyFields() const {
387 int value = used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words();
388 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!IsJSObjectMap(*this), value == 0);
389 int unused;
390 if (value >= JSObject::kFieldsAdded) {
391 unused = instance_size_in_words() - value;
392 } else {
393 // For out of object properties "used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words"
394 // byte encodes the slack in the property array.
395 unused = value;
396 }
397 return unused;
398}
399
400int Map::UnusedInObjectProperties() const {
401 // Like Map::UnusedPropertyFields(), but returns 0 for out of object
402 // properties.
403 int value = used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words();
404 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!IsJSObjectMap(*this), value == 0);
405 if (value >= JSObject::kFieldsAdded) {
406 return instance_size_in_words() - value;
407 }
408 return 0;
409}
410
411int Map::used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words() const {
412 return RELAXED_READ_BYTE_FIELD(*this, kUsedOrUnusedInstanceSizeInWordsOffset);
413}
414
415void Map::set_used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words(int value) {
416 CHECK_LE(static_cast<unsigned>(value), 255);
417 RELAXED_WRITE_BYTE_FIELD(*this, kUsedOrUnusedInstanceSizeInWordsOffset,
418 static_cast<uint8_t>(value));
419}
420
421int Map::UsedInstanceSize() const {
422 int words = used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words();
423 if (words < JSObject::kFieldsAdded) {
424 // All in-object properties are used and the words is tracking the slack
425 // in the property array.
426 return instance_size();
427 }
428 return words * kTaggedSize;
429}
430
431void Map::SetInObjectUnusedPropertyFields(int value) {
432 static_assert(JSObject::kFieldsAdded == JSObject::kHeaderSize / kTaggedSize);
433 if (!IsJSObjectMap(*this)) {
434 CHECK_EQ(0, value);
435 set_used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words(0);
436 DCHECK_EQ(0, UnusedPropertyFields());
437 return;
438 }
439 CHECK_LE(0, value);
440 DCHECK_LE(value, GetInObjectProperties());
441 int used_inobject_properties = GetInObjectProperties() - value;
442 set_used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words(
443 GetInObjectPropertyOffset(used_inobject_properties) / kTaggedSize);
444 DCHECK_EQ(value, UnusedPropertyFields());
445}
446
447void Map::SetOutOfObjectUnusedPropertyFields(int value) {
448 static_assert(JSObject::kFieldsAdded == JSObject::kHeaderSize / kTaggedSize);
449 CHECK_LT(static_cast<unsigned>(value), JSObject::kFieldsAdded);
450 // For out of object properties "used_instance_size_in_words" byte encodes
451 // the slack in the property array.
452 set_used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words(value);
453 DCHECK_EQ(value, UnusedPropertyFields());
454}
455
456void Map::CopyUnusedPropertyFields(Tagged<Map> map) {
457 set_used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words(
458 map->used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words());
459 DCHECK_EQ(UnusedPropertyFields(), map->UnusedPropertyFields());
460}
461
462void Map::CopyUnusedPropertyFieldsAdjustedForInstanceSize(Tagged<Map> map) {
463 int value = map->used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words();
464 if (value >= JSPrimitiveWrapper::kFieldsAdded) {
465 // Unused in-object fields. Adjust the offset from the object’s start
466 // so it matches the distance to the object’s end.
467 value += instance_size_in_words() - map->instance_size_in_words();
468 }
469 set_used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words(value);
470 DCHECK_EQ(UnusedPropertyFields(), map->UnusedPropertyFields());
471}
472
473void Map::AccountAddedPropertyField() {
474 // Update used instance size and unused property fields number.
475 static_assert(JSObject::kFieldsAdded == JSObject::kHeaderSize / kTaggedSize);
476#ifdef DEBUG
477 int new_unused = UnusedPropertyFields() - 1;
478 if (new_unused < 0) new_unused += JSObject::kFieldsAdded;
479#endif
480 int value = used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words();
481 if (value >= JSObject::kFieldsAdded) {
482 if (value == instance_size_in_words()) {
483 AccountAddedOutOfObjectPropertyField(0);
484 } else {
485 // The property is added in-object, so simply increment the counter.
486 set_used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words(value + 1);
487 }
488 } else {
489 AccountAddedOutOfObjectPropertyField(value);
490 }
491 DCHECK_EQ(new_unused, UnusedPropertyFields());
492}
493
494void Map::AccountAddedOutOfObjectPropertyField(int unused_in_property_array) {
495 unused_in_property_array--;
496 if (unused_in_property_array < 0) {
497 unused_in_property_array += JSObject::kFieldsAdded;
498 }
499 CHECK_LT(static_cast<unsigned>(unused_in_property_array),
500 JSObject::kFieldsAdded);
501 set_used_or_unused_instance_size_in_words(unused_in_property_array);
502 DCHECK_EQ(unused_in_property_array, UnusedPropertyFields());
503}

577bool Map::is_abandoned_prototype_map() const {
578 return is_prototype_map() && !owns_descriptors();
579}

581bool Map::should_be_fast_prototype_map() const {
582 DCHECK(is_prototype_map());
583 if (!has_prototype_info()) return false;
584 return PrototypeInfo::cast(prototype_info())->should_be_fast_map();
585}
586
587bool Map::has_prototype_info() const {
588 DCHECK(is_prototype_map());
589 return PrototypeInfo::IsPrototypeInfoFast(prototype_info());
590}
591
592bool Map::TryGetPrototypeInfo(Tagged<PrototypeInfo>* result) const {
593 DCHECK(is_prototype_map());
594 Tagged<Object> maybe_proto_info = prototype_info();
595 if (!PrototypeInfo::IsPrototypeInfoFast(maybe_proto_info)) return false;
596 *result = PrototypeInfo::cast(maybe_proto_info);
597 return true;
598}

600void Map::set_elements_kind(ElementsKind elements_kind) {
601 CHECK_LT(static_cast<int>(elements_kind), kElementsKindCount);
602 set_bit_field2(

703bool Map::CanBeDeprecated() const {
704 for (InternalIndex i : IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
705 PropertyDetails details = instance_descriptors(kRelaxedLoad)->GetDetails(i);
706 if (details.representation().MightCauseMapDeprecation()) return true;
707 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData &&
708 details.location() == PropertyLocation::kDescriptor) {
709 return true;
710 }
711 }
712 return false;
713}

723bool Map::CanTransition() const {
724 // Only JSObject and subtypes have map transitions and back pointers.
725 const InstanceType type = instance_type();
726 // Shared JS objects have fixed shapes and do not transition. Their maps are
727 // either in shared space or RO space.
728 DCHECK_IMPLIES(InstanceTypeChecker::IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(type),
729 InAnySharedSpace(*this));
730 return InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(type) &&
731 !InstanceTypeChecker::IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(type);
732}

759void Map::clear_padding() {
760 if (FIELD_SIZE(kOptionalPaddingOffset) == 0) return;
761 DCHECK_EQ(4, FIELD_SIZE(kOptionalPaddingOffset));
762 memset(reinterpret_cast<void*>(address() + kOptionalPaddingOffset), 0,
763 FIELD_SIZE(kOptionalPaddingOffset));

765
766void Map::AppendDescriptor(Isolate* isolate, Descriptor* desc) {
767 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = instance_descriptors(isolate);
768 int number_of_own_descriptors = NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
769 DCHECK(descriptors->number_of_descriptors() == number_of_own_descriptors);
770 {
771 // The following two operations need to happen before the marking write
772 // barrier.
773 descriptors->Append(desc);
774 SetNumberOfOwnDescriptors(number_of_own_descriptors + 1);
775#ifndef V8_DISABLE_WRITE_BARRIERS
776 WriteBarrier::Marking(descriptors, number_of_own_descriptors + 1);
777#endif
778 }
779 // Properly mark the map if the {desc} is an "interesting symbol".
780 if (desc->GetKey()->IsInteresting(isolate)) {
781 set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
782 }
783 PropertyDetails details = desc->GetDetails();
784 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
785 DCHECK_GT(UnusedPropertyFields(), 0);
786 AccountAddedPropertyField();
787 }
788
789// This function does not support appending double field descriptors and
790// it should never try to (otherwise, layout descriptor must be updated too).
791#ifdef DEBUG
792 DCHECK(details.location() != PropertyLocation::kField ||
793 !details.representation().IsDouble());
794#endif
795}

798bool Map::ConcurrentIsHeapObjectWithMap(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
799 Tagged<Object> object,
800 Tagged<Map> meta_map) {
801 if (!IsHeapObject(object)) return false;
802 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object = HeapObject::cast(object);
803 return heap_object->map(cage_base) == meta_map;
804}

806DEF_GETTER(Map, GetBackPointer, Tagged<HeapObject>) {
807 Tagged<Map> back_pointer;
808 if (TryGetBackPointer(cage_base, &back_pointer)) {
809 return back_pointer;
810 }
811 return GetReadOnlyRoots(cage_base).undefined_value();
812}
813
814bool Map::TryGetBackPointer(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
815 Tagged<Map>* back_pointer) const {
816 Tagged<Object> object = constructor_or_back_pointer(cage_base, kRelaxedLoad);
817 // We don't expect maps from another native context in the transition tree,
818 // so just compare object's map against current map's meta map.
819 Tagged<Map> meta_map = map(cage_base);
820 if (ConcurrentIsHeapObjectWithMap(cage_base, object, meta_map)) {
821 DCHECK(IsMap(object));
822 // Sanity check - only contextful maps can transition.
823 DCHECK(IsNativeContext(meta_map->native_context_or_null()));
824 *back_pointer = Map::cast(object);
825 return true;
826 }
827 // If it was a map that'd mean that there are maps from different native
828 // contexts in the transition tree.
829 DCHECK(!IsMap(object));
830 return false;
831}

838 constructor_or_back_pointer());
839 set_constructor_or_back_pointer(value, mode);

890bool Map::IsPrototypeValidityCellValid() const {
891 Tagged<Object> validity_cell = prototype_validity_cell(kRelaxedLoad);
892 if (IsSmi(validity_cell)) {
893 // Smi validity cells should always be considered valid.
894 DCHECK_EQ(Smi::cast(validity_cell).value(), Map::kPrototypeChainValid);
895 return true;
896 }
897 Tagged<Smi> cell_value = Smi::cast(Cell::cast(validity_cell)->value());
898 return cell_value == Smi::FromInt(Map::kPrototypeChainValid);
899}
900
901DEF_GETTER(Map, GetConstructorRaw, Tagged<Object>) {
902 Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = constructor_or_back_pointer(cage_base);
903 // Follow any back pointers.
904 // We don't expect maps from another native context in the transition tree,
905 // so just compare object's map against current map's meta map.
906 Tagged<Map> meta_map = map(cage_base);
907 while (
908 ConcurrentIsHeapObjectWithMap(cage_base, maybe_constructor, meta_map)) {
909 DCHECK(IsMap(maybe_constructor));
910 // Sanity check - only contextful maps can transition.
911 DCHECK(IsNativeContext(meta_map->native_context_or_null()));
912 maybe_constructor =
913 Map::cast(maybe_constructor)->constructor_or_back_pointer(cage_base);
914 }
915 // If it was a map that'd mean that there are maps from different native
916 // contexts in the transition tree.
917 DCHECK(!IsMap(maybe_constructor));
918 return maybe_constructor;
919}
920
921DEF_GETTER(Map, GetNonInstancePrototype, Tagged<Object>) {
922 DCHECK(has_non_instance_prototype());
923 Tagged<Object> raw_constructor = GetConstructorRaw(cage_base);
924 CHECK(IsTuple2(raw_constructor));
925 // Get prototype from the {constructor, non-instance_prototype} tuple.
926 Tagged<Tuple2> non_instance_prototype_constructor_tuple =
927 Tuple2::cast(raw_constructor);
928 Tagged<Object> result = non_instance_prototype_constructor_tuple->value2();
929 DCHECK(!IsJSReceiver(result));
930 DCHECK(!IsFunctionTemplateInfo(result));
931 return result;
932}
933
934DEF_GETTER(Map, GetConstructor, Tagged<Object>) {
935 Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = GetConstructorRaw(cage_base);
936 if (IsTuple2(maybe_constructor)) {
937 // Get constructor from the {constructor, non-instance_prototype} tuple.
938 maybe_constructor = Tuple2::cast(maybe_constructor)->value1();
939 }
940 return maybe_constructor;
941}
942
943Tagged<Object> Map::TryGetConstructor(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
944 int max_steps) {
945 Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = constructor_or_back_pointer(cage_base);
946 // Follow any back pointers.
947 while (IsMap(maybe_constructor, cage_base)) {
948 if (max_steps-- == 0) return Smi::FromInt(0);
949 maybe_constructor =
950 Map::cast(maybe_constructor)->constructor_or_back_pointer(cage_base);
951 }
952 if (IsTuple2(maybe_constructor)) {
953 // Get constructor from the {constructor, non-instance_prototype} tuple.
954 maybe_constructor = Tuple2::cast(maybe_constructor)->value1();
955 }
956 return maybe_constructor;
957}
958
959DEF_GETTER(Map, GetFunctionTemplateInfo, Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo>) {
960 Tagged<Object> constructor = GetConstructor(cage_base);
961 if (IsJSFunction(constructor, cage_base)) {
962 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi =
963 JSFunction::cast(constructor)->shared(cage_base);
964 DCHECK(sfi->IsApiFunction());
965 return sfi->api_func_data();
966 }
967 DCHECK(IsFunctionTemplateInfo(constructor, cage_base));
968 return FunctionTemplateInfo::cast(constructor);
969}

971void Map::SetConstructor(Tagged<Object> constructor, WriteBarrierMode mode) {
972 // Never overwrite a back pointer with a constructor.
973 CHECK(!IsMap(constructor_or_back_pointer()));
974 // Constructor field must contain {constructor, non-instance_prototype} tuple
975 // for maps with non-instance prototype.
976 DCHECK_EQ(has_non_instance_prototype(), IsTuple2(constructor));
977 set_constructor_or_back_pointer(constructor, mode);
978}

986bool Map::IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress() const {
987 return construction_counter() != Map::kNoSlackTracking;
988}
989
990void Map::InobjectSlackTrackingStep(Isolate* isolate) {
991 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
992 // Slack tracking should only be performed on an initial map.
993 DCHECK(IsUndefined(GetBackPointer()));
994 if (!this->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress()) return;
995 int counter = construction_counter();
996 set_construction_counter(counter - 1);
997 if (counter == kSlackTrackingCounterEnd) {
998 MapUpdater::CompleteInobjectSlackTracking(isolate, *this);
999 }
1000}

1002int Map::SlackForArraySize(int old_size, int size_limit) {
1003 const int max_slack = size_limit - old_size;
1004 CHECK_LE(0, max_slack);
1005 if (old_size < 4) {
1006 DCHECK_LE(1, max_slack);
1007 return 1;
1008 }
1009 return std::min(max_slack, old_size / 4);
1010}

1012int Map::InstanceSizeFromSlack(int slack) const {
1013 return instance_size() - slack * kTaggedSize;
1014}
